lispMIB.name: lispMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of the IETF LISP-MIB module. Published as RFC 7052.

lispMIB.organization: IETF Locator/ID Separation Protocol (LISP) Working Group
lispMIB.description: This MIB module contains managed objects to support monitoring devices that support the Locator/ID Separation Protocol (LISP). LispAddressType.name: LispAddressType
LispAddressType.description: LISP architecture can be applied to a wide variety of address-families. This textual-convention is a generalization for representing addresses belonging to those address-families. For convenience, this document refers to any such address as a LISP address. LispAddressType textual-convention consists of the following four-tuple: 1. IANA Address Family Number: A field of length 2 octets, whose value is of the form following the assigned AddressFamilyNumbers textual-convention described in IANA-ADDRESS-FAMILY-NUMBERS-MIB DEFINITIONS, available from http://www.iana.org/assignments/ianaaddressfamilynumbers-mib. The enumerations are also listed in [IANA]. Note that this list of address family numbers is maintained by IANA. 2. Length of LISP address: A field of length 1 octet, whose value indicates the octet-length of the next (third) field of this LispAddressType four-tuple. 3. LISP address: A field of variable length as indicated in the previous (second) field, whose value is an address of the IANA Address Family indicated in the first field of this LispAddressType four-tuple. Note that any of the IANA Address Families can be represented. Particularly when the address family is LISP Canonical Address Format (LCAF) with IANA-assigned Address Family Number 16387, then the first octet of this field indicates the LCAF type, and the rest of this field is same as the encoding format of the LISP Canonical Address after the length field, as defined in LCAF document. 4. Mask-length of address: A field of length 1 octet, whose value is the mask-length to be applied to the LISP address specified in the previous (third) field. To illustrate the use of this object, consider the LISP MIB Object below titled lispMapCacheEntry. This object begins with the following entities: lispMapCacheEntry ::= SEQUENCE { lispMapCacheEidLength INTEGER, lispMapCacheEid LispAddressType, ... [skip] ... Example 1: Suppose that the IPv4 EID-Prefix stored is 192.0.2.0/24. In this case, the values within lispMapCacheEntry would be: lispMapCacheEidLength = 8 lispMapCacheEid = 1, 4, 192.0.2.0, 24 ... [skip] ... where 8 is the total length in octets of the next object (lispMapCacheEID of type LispAddressType). Then, the value 1 indicates the IPv4 AF (per the IANA-ADDRESS-FAMILY-NUMBERS-MIB), the value 4 indicates that the AF is 4 octets in length, 192.0.2.0 is the IPv4 address, and the value 24 is the mask-length in bits. Note that the lispMapCacheEidLength value of 8 is used to compute the length of the fourth (last) field in lispMapCacheEid to be 1 octet -- as computed by 8 - (2 + 1 + 4) = 1. Example 2: Suppose that the IPv6 EID-Prefix stored is 2001:db8:a::/48. In this case, the values within lispMapCacheEntry would be: lispMapCacheEidLength = 20 lispMapCacheEid = 2, 16, 2001:db8:a::, 48 ... [skip] ... where 20 is the total length in octets of the next object (lispMapCacheEID of type LispAddressType). Then, the value 2 indicates the IPv6 AF (per the IANA-ADDRESS-FAMILY-NUMBERS-MIB), the value 16 indicates that the AF is 16 octets in length, 2001:db8:a:: is the IPv6 address, and the value 48 is the mask-length in bits. Note that the lispMapCacheEidLength value of 20 is used to compute the length of the fourth (last) field in lispMapCacheEid to be 1 octet -- as computed by 20 - (2 + 1 + 16) = 1. Example 3: As an example where LCAF is used, suppose that the IPv4 EID-Prefix stored is 192.0.2.0/24 and it is part of LISP Instance ID 101. In this case, the values within lispMapCacheEntry would be: lispMapCacheEidLength = 11 lispMapCacheEid = 16387, 7, 2, 101, 1, 192.0.2.0, 24 ... [skip] ... where 11 is the total length in octets of the next object (lispMapCacheEID of type LispAddressType). Then, the value 16387 indicates the LCAF AF (see the IANA-ADDRESS-FAMILY-NUMBERS-MIB), the value 7 indicates that the LCAF AF is 7 octets in length in this case, 2 indicates that LCAF Type 2 encoding is used (see the LCAF document), 101 gives the Instance ID, 1 gives the AFI (per the IANA-ADDRESS-FAMILY-NUMBERS-MIB) for an IPv4 address, 192.0.2.0 is the IPv4 address, and 24 is the mask-length in bits. Note that the lispMapCacheEidLength value of 11 octets is used to compute the length of the last field in lispMapCacheEid to be 1 octet -- as computed by 11 - (2 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 4) = 1. Note: all LISP header formats and locations of specific flags, bits, and fields are as given in the base LISP references of RFC 6830, RFC 6832, and RFC 6833.
LispAddressType.reference: RFC 6830, Section 14.2 and LISP Canonical Address Format (LCAF), Work in Progress, March 2013.

lispFeaturesTable.name: lispFeaturesTable
lispFeaturesTable.description: This table represents the ON/OFF status of the various LISP features that can be enabled on LISP devices.

lispFeaturesEntry.name: lispFeaturesEntry
lispFeaturesEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the lispFeaturesTable.

lispFeaturesInstanceID.name: lispFeaturesInstanceID
lispFeaturesInstanceID.description: This represents the Instance ID of the LISP header. An Instance ID in the LISP address encoding helps uniquely identify the AFI-based address space to which a given EID belongs. Its default value is 0.

lispFeaturesAddressFamily.name: lispFeaturesAddressFamily
lispFeaturesAddressFamily.description: The IANA Address Family Number of destination address of packets that this LISP device is enabled to process.

lispFeaturesItrEnabled.name: lispFeaturesItrEnabled
lispFeaturesItrEnabled.description: Indicates the status of ITR role on this device. If this object is true, then the ITR feature is enabled.

lispFeaturesEtrEnabled.name: lispFeaturesEtrEnabled
lispFeaturesEtrEnabled.description: Indicates the status of ETR role on this device. If this object is true, then the ETR feature is enabled.

lispFeaturesProxyItrEnabled.name: lispFeaturesProxyItrEnabled
lispFeaturesProxyItrEnabled.description: Indicates the status of Proxy-ITR role on this device. If this object is true, then the Proxy-ITR feature is enabled.

lispFeaturesProxyEtrEnabled.name: lispFeaturesProxyEtrEnabled
lispFeaturesProxyEtrEnabled.description: Indicates the status of Proxy-ETR role on this device. If this object is true, then the Proxy-ETR feature is enabled.

lispFeaturesMapServerEnabled.name: lispFeaturesMapServerEnabled
lispFeaturesMapServerEnabled.description: Indicates the status of Map Server role on this device. If this object is true, then the Map-Server feature is enabled.

lispFeaturesMapResolverEnabled.name: lispFeaturesMapResolverEnabled
lispFeaturesMapResolverEnabled.description: Indicates the status of Map Resolver role on this device. If this object is true, then Map-Resolver feature is enabled.

lispFeaturesMapCacheSize.name: lispFeaturesMapCacheSize
lispFeaturesMapCacheSize.description: Size of EID-to-RLOC map-cache on this device.

lispFeaturesMapCacheLimit.name: lispFeaturesMapCacheLimit
lispFeaturesMapCacheLimit.description: Maximum permissible entries in EID-to-RLOC map-cache on this device.

lispFeaturesEtrMapCacheTtl.name: lispFeaturesEtrMapCacheTtl
lispFeaturesEtrMapCacheTtl.description: The stored Record TTL of the EID-to-RLOC map record in the map-cache.

lispFeaturesRlocProbeEnabled.name: lispFeaturesRlocProbeEnabled
lispFeaturesRlocProbeEnabled.description: Indicates the status of RLOC-Probing feature on this device. If this object is true, then this feature is enabled.

lispFeaturesEtrAcceptMapDataEnabled.name: lispFeaturesEtrAcceptMapDataEnabled
lispFeaturesEtrAcceptMapDataEnabled.description: Indicates the status of accepting piggybacked mapping data received in a map-request on this device. If this object is true, then this device accepts piggybacked mapping data.

lispFeaturesEtrAcceptMapDataVerifyEnable.name: lispFeaturesEtrAcceptMapDataVerifyEnabled
lispFeaturesEtrAcceptMapDataVerifyEnable.description: Indicates the status of verifying accepted piggybacked mapping data received in a map-request on this device. If this object is true, then this device verifies accepted piggybacked mapping data.

lispFeaturesRouterTimeStamp.name: lispFeaturesRouterTimeStamp
lispFeaturesRouterTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at which the LISP feature was enabled on this device. If this information was present at the most recent reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

lispIidToVrfTable.name: lispIidToVrfTable
lispIidToVrfTable.description: This table represents the mapping of a LISP Instance ID to a VRF.

lispIidToVrfEntry.name: lispIidToVrfEntry
lispIidToVrfEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the lispIidToVrfTable.

lispIidToVrfName.name: lispIidToVrfName
lispIidToVrfName.description: The identifier for each VPN that is mapped to the given LISP Instance ID.

lispGlobalStatsTable.name: lispGlobalStatsTable
lispGlobalStatsTable.description: This table provides global statistics for a given Instance ID per address family on a LISP device.

lispGlobalStatsEntry.name: lispGlobalStatsEntry
lispGlobalStatsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the lispGlobalStatsTable.

lispGlobalStatsMapRequestsIn.name: lispGlobalStatsMapRequestsIn
lispGlobalStatsMapRequestsIn.description: Total number of map requests received by this device for any EID-Prefix of the given address family and Instance ID. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of LISP features being removed, which can be detected by observing the value of lispFeaturesRouterTimeStamp.

lispGlobalStatsMapRequestsOut.name: lispGlobalStatsMapRequestsOut
lispGlobalStatsMapRequestsOut.description: Total number of map requests sent by this device for any EID-Prefix of the given address family and Instance ID. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of LISP features being removed, which can be detected by observing the value of lispFeaturesRouterTimeStamp.

lispGlobalStatsMapRepliesIn.name: lispGlobalStatsMapRepliesIn
lispGlobalStatsMapRepliesIn.description: Total number of map replies received by this device for any EID-Prefix of the given address family and Instance ID. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of LISP features being removed, which can be detected by observing the value of lispFeaturesRouterTimeStamp.

lispGlobalStatsMapRepliesOut.name: lispGlobalStatsMapRepliesOut
lispGlobalStatsMapRepliesOut.description: Total number of map replies sent by this device for any EID prefix of the given address family and Instance ID. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of LISP features being removed, which can be detected by observing the value of lispFeaturesRouterTimeStamp.

lispGlobalStatsMapRegistersIn.name: lispGlobalStatsMapRegistersIn
lispGlobalStatsMapRegistersIn.description: Total number of map registers received by this device for any EID-Prefix of the given address family and Instance ID. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of LISP features being removed, which can be detected by observing the value of lispFeaturesRouterTimeStamp.

lispGlobalStatsMapRegistersOut.name: lispGlobalStatsMapRegistersOut
lispGlobalStatsMapRegistersOut.description: Total number of map registers sent by this device for any EID-Prefix of the given address family and Instance ID. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of LISP features being removed, which can be detected by observing the value of lispFeaturesRouterTimeStamp.

lispMappingDatabaseTable.name: lispMappingDatabaseTable
lispMappingDatabaseTable.description: This table represents the EID-to-RLOC mapping database that contains the EID-Prefix to RLOC mappings configured on an ETR. This table represents all such mappings for the given LISP site to which this device belongs.

lispMappingDatabaseEidLength.name: lispMappingDatabaseEidLength
lispMappingDatabaseEidLength.description: This object gives the octet-length of lispMappingDatabaseEid.

lispMappingDatabaseEid.name: lispMappingDatabaseEid
lispMappingDatabaseEid.description: The EID-Prefix of the mapping database.

lispMappingDatabaseLsb.name: lispMappingDatabaseLsb
lispMappingDatabaseLsb.description: The locator status bits for this EID-Prefix.

lispMappingDatabaseEidPartitioned.name: lispMappingDatabaseEidPartitioned
lispMappingDatabaseEidPartitioned.description: Indicates if this device is partitioned from the site that contains this EID-Prefix. If this object is true, then it means this device is partitioned from the site.

lispMappingDatabaseTimeStamp.name: lispMappingDatabaseTimeStamp
lispMappingDatabaseTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at which the EID Prefix information represented by this mapping database entry was configured on this device. If this information was present at the most recent reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

lispMappingDatabaseDecapOctets.name: lispMappingDatabaseDecapOctets
lispMappingDatabaseDecapOctets.description: The number of octets, after decapsulation, of LISP packets that were decapsulated by this device addressed to a host within this EID-Prefix. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of LISP features being removed, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMappingDatabaseTimeStamp.

lispMappingDatabaseDecapPackets.name: lispMappingDatabaseDecapPackets
lispMappingDatabaseDecapPackets.description: The number of LISP packets that were decapsulated by this device addressed to a host within this EID-Prefix. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of LISP features being removed, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMappingDatabaseTimeStamp.

lispMappingDatabaseEncapOctets.name: lispMappingDatabaseEncapOctets
lispMappingDatabaseEncapOctets.description: The number of octets, before encapsulation, of LISP packets that were encapsulated by this device, whose inner header source address matched this EID-Prefix. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of LISP features being removed, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMappingDatabaseTimeStamp.

lispMappingDatabaseEncapPackets.name: lispMappingDatabaseEncapPackets
lispMappingDatabaseEncapPackets.description: The number of LISP packets that were encapsulated by this device whose inner header source address matched this EID prefix. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of LISP features being removed, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMappingDatabaseTimeStamp.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorTable.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorTable
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorTable.description: This table represents the set of routing locators per EID prefix contained in the EID-to-RLOC database configured on this ETR.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorEntry.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorEntry
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the lispMappingDatabaseLocatorTable.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocLength.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocLength
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocLength.description: This object is used to get the octet-length of lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRloc.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRloc.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRloc
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRloc.description: This object is a locator for the given EID-Prefix in the mapping database.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocPriority.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocPriority
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocPriority.description: The unicast priority of the RLOC.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocWeight.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocWeight
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocWeight.description: The unicast weight of the RLOC.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocMPriority.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocMPriority
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocMPriority.description: The multicast priority of the RLOC.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocMWeight.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocMWeight
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocMWeight.description: The multicast weight of the RLOC.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocState.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocState
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocState.description: The state of this RLOC as per this device. (1 = RLOC is up; 2 = RLOC is down; 3 = RLOC is unreachable).

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocLocal.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocLocal
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocLocal.description: Indicates whether the RLOC is local to this device (or remote, meaning local to another device in the same LISP site). (1 = RLOC is an address on this device; 2 = RLOC is an address on another device).

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocTimeStamp.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocTimeStamp
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at which the RLOC of the EID Prefix represented by this mapping database entry was configured on this device. If this information was present at the most recent reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocDecapOctet.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocDecapOctets
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocDecapOctet.description: The number of octets of LISP packets that were addressed to this RLOC of the EID-Prefix and were decapsulated. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of database mappings getting reconfigured or RLOC status changes, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocDecapPacke.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocDecapPackets
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocDecapPacke.description: The number of LISP packets that were addressed to this RLOC of the EID-Prefix and were decapsulated. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of database mappings getting reconfigured or RLOC status changes, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocEncapOctet.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocEncapOctets
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocEncapOctet.description: The number of octets of LISP packets that were encapsulated by this device using this RLOC address as the source, and that were sourced by an address of this EID-Prefix. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of database mappings getting reconfigured or RLOC status changes, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocEncapPacke.name: lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocEncapPackets
lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocEncapPacke.description: The number of LISP packets that were encapsulated by this device using this RLOC address as the source and that were sourced by an address of this EID-Prefix. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of database mappings getting reconfigured or RLOC status changes, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMappingDatabaseLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispMapCacheTable.name: lispMapCacheTable
lispMapCacheTable.description: This table represents the short-lived, on-demand table on an ITR that stores, tracks, and is responsible for timing-out and otherwise validating EID-to-RLOC mappings.

lispMapCacheEntry.name: lispMapCacheEntry
lispMapCacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the lispMapCacheTable.

lispMapCacheEidLength.name: lispMapCacheEidLength
lispMapCacheEidLength.description: This object is used to get the octet-length of lispMapCacheEid.

lispMapCacheEid.name: lispMapCacheEid
lispMapCacheEid.description: The EID-Prefix in the mapping cache.

lispMapCacheEidTimeStamp.name: lispMapCacheEidTimeStamp
lispMapCacheEidTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at which the EID Prefix information represented by this entry was learned by this device. If this information was present at the most recent reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

lispMapCacheEidExpiryTime.name: lispMapCacheEidExpiryTime
lispMapCacheEidExpiryTime.description: The time remaining before the ITR times-out this EID-Prefix.

lispMapCacheEidState.name: lispMapCacheEidState
lispMapCacheEidState.description: This object is used to indicate the activity of this EID prefix. If this object is true, then it means this EID prefix is seeing activity.

lispMapCacheEidAuthoritative.name: lispMapCacheEidAuthoritative
lispMapCacheEidAuthoritative.description: This object is used to indicate whether the EID-Prefix was installed by an authoritative map-reply. If this object is true, then it means this EID-Prefix was installed by an authoritative map-reply.

lispMapCacheEidDecapOctets.name: lispMapCacheEidDecapOctets
lispMapCacheEidDecapOctets.description: The number of octets of LISP packets that were decapsulated by this device and were sourced from a remote host within this EID-Prefix. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of cache being removed and replaced, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMapCacheEidTimeStamp.

lispMapCacheEidDecapPackets.name: lispMapCacheEidDecapPackets
lispMapCacheEidDecapPackets.description: The number of LISP packets that were decapsulated by this device and were sourced from a remote host within this EID-Prefix. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of cache being removed and replaced, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMapCacheEidTimeStamp.

lispMapCacheEidEncapOctets.name: lispMapCacheEidEncapOctets
lispMapCacheEidEncapOctets.description: The number of octets of LISP packets that were encapsulated by this device using the given EID-Prefix in the map-cache. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of cache being removed and replaced, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMapCacheEidTimeStamp.

lispMapCacheEidEncapPackets.name: lispMapCacheEidEncapPackets
lispMapCacheEidEncapPackets.description: The number of LISP packets that were encapsulated by this device using the given EID-Prefix in the map-cache. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of cache being removed and replaced, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMapCacheEidTimeStamp.

lispMapCacheLocatorTable.name: lispMapCacheLocatorTable
lispMapCacheLocatorTable.description: This table represents the set of locators per EID-Prefix contained in the map-cache table of an ITR.

lispMapCacheLocatorEntry.name: lispMapCacheLocatorEntry
lispMapCacheLocatorEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the lispMapCacheLocatorTable.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLength.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLength
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLength.description: This object is used to get the octet-length of lispMapCacheLocatorRloc.

lispMapCacheLocatorRloc.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRloc
lispMapCacheLocatorRloc.description: The locator for the EID-Prefix in the mapping cache.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocPriority.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocPriority
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocPriority.description: The unicast priority of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix (0-255); lower is more preferred.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocWeight.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocWeight
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocWeight.description: The unicast weight of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix (0 - 100) percentage.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocMPriority.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocMPriority
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocMPriority.description: The multicast priority of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix (0-255); lower is more preferred.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocMWeight.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocMWeight
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocMWeight.description: The multicast weight of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix (0 - 100) percentage.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocState.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocState
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocState.description: The state of this RLOC as per this device (1 = RLOC is up; 2 = RLOC is down; 3 = RLOC is unreachable).

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocTimeStamp.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocTimeStamp
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at which the RLOC of EID-Prefix information represented by this entry was learned by this device. If this information was present at the most recent reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastPriorityChang.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastPriorityChange
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastPriorityChang.description: Time elapsed since the last change of the unicast priority of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix. Note that this is independent of lispMapCacheLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastWeightChange.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastWeightChange
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastWeightChange.description: Time elapsed since the last change of the unicast weight of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix. Note that this is independent of lispMapCacheLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastMPriorityChan.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastMPriorityChange
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastMPriorityChan.description: Time since the last change of the multicast priority of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastMWeightChange.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastMWeightChange
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastMWeightChange.description: Time since the last change of the multicast weight of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastStateChange.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastStateChange
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocLastStateChange.description: Time since the last change of the up/down state of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocRtt.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocRtt
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocRtt.description: Round-trip time of RLOC probe and map-reply for this RLOC address for this prefix.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocDecapOctets.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocDecapOctets
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocDecapOctets.description: The number of octets of LISP packets that were decapsulated by this device and were sourced from a remote host within this EID-Prefix and were encapsulated for this RLOC. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of RLOC of cache being removed and replaced, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMapCacheLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocDecapPackets.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocDecapPackets
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocDecapPackets.description: The number of LISP packets that were decapsulated by this device and were sourced from a remote host within this EID-Prefix and were encapsulated for this RLOC. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of RLOC of cache being removed and replaced, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMapCacheLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocEncapOctets.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocEncapOctets
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocEncapOctets.description: The number of octets of LISP packets that matched this EID-Prefix and were encapsulated using this RLOC address. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of RLOC of cache being removed and replaced, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMapCacheLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispMapCacheLocatorRlocEncapPackets.name: lispMapCacheLocatorRlocEncapPackets
lispMapCacheLocatorRlocEncapPackets.description: The number of LISP packets that matched this EID-Prefix and were encapsulated using this RLOC address. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of RLOC of cache being removed and replaced, which can be detected by observing the value of lispMapCacheLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispConfiguredLocatorTable.name: lispConfiguredLocatorTable
lispConfiguredLocatorTable.description: This table represents the set of routing locators configured on this device. Note that the addresses configured by Proxy-ITR are treated as routing locators and therefore can be part of this table.

lispConfiguredLocatorEntry.name: lispConfiguredLocatorEntry
lispConfiguredLocatorEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the lispConfiguredLocatorTable.

lispConfiguredLocatorRlocLength.name: lispConfiguredLocatorRlocLength
lispConfiguredLocatorRlocLength.description: This object is used to get the octet-length of lispConfiguredLocatorRloc.

lispConfiguredLocatorRloc.name: lispConfiguredLocatorRloc
lispConfiguredLocatorRloc.description: This object is an RLOC address configured on this device. It can be an RLOC that is local to this device or can be an RLOC that belongs to another ETR within the same site. Proxy-ITR address is treated as an RLOC.

lispConfiguredLocatorRlocState.name: lispConfiguredLocatorRlocState
lispConfiguredLocatorRlocState.description: The state of this RLOC as per this device. (1 = RLOC is up; 2 = RLOC is down; 3 = RLOC is unreachable).

lispConfiguredLocatorRlocLocal.name: lispConfiguredLocatorRlocLocal
lispConfiguredLocatorRlocLocal.description: Indicates whether the RLOC is local to this device (or remote, meaning local to another device in the same LISP site). (1 = RLOC is an address on this device; 2 = RLOC is an address on another device).

lispConfiguredLocatorRlocTimeStamp.name: lispConfiguredLocatorRlocTimeStamp
lispConfiguredLocatorRlocTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at which the RLOC was configured on this device. If this information was present at the most recent reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

lispConfiguredLocatorRlocDecapOctets.name: lispConfiguredLocatorRlocDecapOctets
lispConfiguredLocatorRlocDecapOctets.description: The number of octets of LISP packets that were addressed to this RLOC and were decapsulated. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of configured RLOC being removed and replaced, which can be detected by observing the value of lispConfiguredLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispConfiguredLocatorRlocDecapPackets.name: lispConfiguredLocatorRlocDecapPackets
lispConfiguredLocatorRlocDecapPackets.description: The number of LISP packets that were addressed to this RLOC and were decapsulated. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of configured RLOC being removed and replaced, which can be detected by observing the value of lispConfiguredLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispConfiguredLocatorRlocEncapOctets.name: lispConfiguredLocatorRlocEncapOctets
lispConfiguredLocatorRlocEncapOctets.description: The number of octets of LISP packets that were encapsulated by this device using this RLOC address as the source. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of configured RLOC being removed and replaced, which can be detected by observing the value of lispConfiguredLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispConfiguredLocatorRlocEncapPackets.name: lispConfiguredLocatorRlocEncapPackets
lispConfiguredLocatorRlocEncapPackets.description: The number of LISP packets that were encapsulated by this device using this RLOC address as the source. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of configured RLOC being removed and replaced, which can be detected by observing the value of lispConfiguredLocatorRlocTimeStamp.

lispEidRegistrationTable.name: lispEidRegistrationTable
lispEidRegistrationTable.description: This table provides the properties of each LISP EID-Prefix that is registered with this device when configured to be a Map-Server.

lispEidRegistrationEntry.name: lispEidRegistrationEntry
lispEidRegistrationEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the lispEidRegistrationTable.

lispEidRegistrationEidLength.name: lispEidRegistrationEidLength
lispEidRegistrationEidLength.description: This object is used to get the octet-length of lispEidRegistrationEid.

lispEidRegistrationEid.name: lispEidRegistrationEid
lispEidRegistrationEid.description: The EID-Prefix that is being registered.

lispEidRegistrationSiteName.name: lispEidRegistrationSiteName
lispEidRegistrationSiteName.description: Site name used by a Map-Server to distinguish different LISP sites that are registering with it.

lispEidRegistrationSiteDescription.name: lispEidRegistrationSiteDescription
lispEidRegistrationSiteDescription.description: Description for a site name used by a Map-Server. The EID prefix that is being registered belongs to this site.

lispEidRegistrationIsRegistered.name: lispEidRegistrationIsRegistered
lispEidRegistrationIsRegistered.description: Indicates the registration status of the given EID-Prefix. If this object is true, then it means the EID-Prefix is registered. The value false implies the EID-Prefix is not registered with the Map Server. There are multiple scenarios when this could happen like authentication failures, routing problems, misconfigs to name a few.

lispEidRegistrationFirstTimeStamp.name: lispEidRegistrationFirstTimeStamp
lispEidRegistrationFirstTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at which the first valid register message for the EID Prefix information represented by this entry was received by this device. If this information was present at the most recent reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

lispEidRegistrationLastTimeStamp.name: lispEidRegistrationLastTimeStamp
lispEidRegistrationLastTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime at which the last valid register message for the EID Prefix information represented by this entry was received by this device. If this information was present at the most recent reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

lispEidRegistrationLastRegisterSenderLen.name: lispEidRegistrationLastRegisterSenderLength
lispEidRegistrationLastRegisterSenderLen.description: This object is used to get the octet-length of lispEidRegistrationLastRegisterSender, the next object.

lispEidRegistrationLastRegisterSender.name: lispEidRegistrationLastRegisterSender
lispEidRegistrationLastRegisterSender.description: Source address of the last valid register message for the given EID-Prefix that was received by this device.

lispEidRegistrationAuthenticationErrors.name: lispEidRegistrationAuthenticationErrors
lispEidRegistrationAuthenticationErrors.description: Count of total authentication errors of map-registers received for the given EID-Prefix. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of site config changes, which can be detected by observing the value of lispEidRegistrationFirstTimeStamp.

lispEidRegistrationRlocsMismatch.name: lispEidRegistrationRlocsMismatch
lispEidRegistrationRlocsMismatch.description: Count of total map-registers received that had at least one RLOC that was not in the allowed list of RLOCs for the given EID-Prefix. Discontinuities in this monotonically increasing value occur at reinitialization of the management system. Discontinuities can also occur as a result of site config changes, which can be detected by observing the value of lispEidRegistrationFirstTimeStamp.

lispEidRegistrationEtrTable.name: lispEidRegistrationEtrTable
lispEidRegistrationEtrTable.description: This table provides the properties of ETRs that register the given EID-Prefix with this device when configured to be a Map-Server.

lispEidRegistrationEtrEntry.name: lispEidRegistrationEtrEntry
lispEidRegistrationEtrEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the lispEidRegistrationEtrTable.

lispEidRegistrationEtrSenderLength.name: lispEidRegistrationEtrSenderLength
lispEidRegistrationEtrSenderLength.description: This object is used to get the octet-length of lispEidRegistrationEtrSender.

lispEidRegistrationEtrSender.name: lispEidRegistrationEtrSender
lispEidRegistrationEtrSender.description: Source address of the ETR that is sending valid register messages for this EID-Prefix to this device.

lispEidRegistrationEtrLastTimeStamp.name: lispEidRegistrationEtrLastTimeStamp

If this information was present at the most recent reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

lispEidRegistrationEtrTtl.name: lispEidRegistrationEtrTtl
lispEidRegistrationEtrTtl.description: The Record TTL of the registering ETR device for this EID-Prefix.

lispEidRegistrationEtrProxyReply.name: lispEidRegistrationEtrProxyReply
lispEidRegistrationEtrProxyReply.description: Indicates proxy-replying status of the registering ETR for this EID-Prefix. If this object is true, then it means the Map-Server can proxy-reply.

lispEidRegistrationEtrWantsMapNotify.name: lispEidRegistrationEtrWantsMapNotify
lispEidRegistrationEtrWantsMapNotify.description: Indicates whether the EID-Prefix wants Map-Notifications. If this object is true, then it means the EID-Prefix wants Map-Notifications.

lispEidRegistrationLocatorEntry.name: lispEidRegistrationLocatorEntry
lispEidRegistrationLocatorEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the lispEidRegistrationLocatorTable.

lispEidRegistrationLocatorRlocLength.description: This object is used to get the octet-length of lispEidRegistrationLocatorRloc.

lispEidRegistrationLocatorRloc.name: lispEidRegistrationLocatorRloc
lispEidRegistrationLocatorRloc.description: The locator of the given EID-Prefix being registered by the given ETR with this device.

lispEidRegistrationLocatorRlocState.name: lispEidRegistrationLocatorRlocState
lispEidRegistrationLocatorRlocState.description: The cached state of this RLOC received in map-register from the ETR by the device, in the capacity of a Map-Server. Value 1 refers to up, value 2 refers to down.

lispEidRegistrationLocatorIsLocal.name: lispEidRegistrationLocatorIsLocal
lispEidRegistrationLocatorIsLocal.description: Indicates if the given locator is local to the registering ETR. If this object is true, it means the locator is local.

lispEidRegistrationLocatorPriority.name: lispEidRegistrationLocatorPriority
lispEidRegistrationLocatorPriority.description: The unicast priority of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix in the register message sent by the given ETR.

lispEidRegistrationLocatorWeight.name: lispEidRegistrationLocatorWeight
lispEidRegistrationLocatorWeight.description: The unicast weight of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix in the register message sent by the given ETR.

lispEidRegistrationLocatorMPriority.name: lispEidRegistrationLocatorMPriority
lispEidRegistrationLocatorMPriority.description: The multicast priority of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix in the register message sent by the given ETR.

lispEidRegistrationLocatorMWeight.name: lispEidRegistrationLocatorMWeight
lispEidRegistrationLocatorMWeight.description: The multicast weight of the RLOC for this EID-Prefix in the register message sent by the given ETR.

lispUseMapServerTable.description: This table provides the properties of the Map-Server(s) with which this device is configured to register.
